title: For Sale/Trade:  Wicked Lasers Spyder Arctic III 1 Watt blue laser. Burns/Cuts/Melts
postcontent:
This is a brand new Wicked Lasers Spyder III Arctic 1 watt blue laser. Right off the bat, I'll tell you that you can go on to Wicked Laser's website right now and order this very laser for $299.99. However, I won't take anything close to that. The FDA (yes FDA) has put an import ban on any handheld laser above 5mw. This particular laser is 200x more powerful then what current import allows. Actually getting your hands on one of these is VERY diffcult. I'm a GM for UPS and even with my connections in customs, it still took me 6 1/2 months to get a hold of mine. From what I'm told 85% of these are seized.

However, once you DO have one, they are pretty incredible. It will burn or melt most things dark colored. You can cut through plastics, light cigs, pop ballons, start fires, etc. The beam is so powerful that if you pointed it straight up in the air, no only can you see the beam the entire way up, but the only reason it doesn't hit outter space is because our inner atmosphere diffuses the beam. If you were at sea, and pointed the beam straight out infront of you, the only reason you aren't able to see it past a certain point is because of the curvature of the Earth.

I understand this isn't what you typically see, so if you have any questions feel free to ask.

title: For Sale:  New Slide fire / bump fire AR-15 stock
location: Green Bay, Wisconsin, Ohio, United States
postcontent:
Shoot faster than you ever thought possible! ATF approved and legal! Must see the amazing video of how this product works to believe it. Designed for use with your AR-15 rifle with collapsing buttstock. A conversion kit is available for solid/fixed stocks.

The Slide Fire Solutions' ground breaking "Slide Stock" technology and ergonomic design provide individuals the ability to Slide Fire more safely - offering another element of entertainment for recreational shooters everywhere!

Please note this is a bump fire device that significantly increases your trigger pull speed, but does not convert your gun into a machine gun. Folks these really work well and are not a gimmick and we have tons of happy customers some buying  several units for their collection of  AR15 rifles.

Applying principles that have been used for over 40 years to Bump Fire - this new radical design ensures the operator can hold the rifle correctly without compromising their own safety or the safety of others around them.  Unlike when bump firing from the hip; the SSAR-15 allows the shooter to properly hold the firearm.  In addition, as a result of the shooter having to push forward to discharge each round, they are able to correct their point-of-aim for each shot discharged instead of allowing recoil to push the muzzle upward in an unsafe direction.

In principal the SSAR-15 functions very similar to the Gatlin or crank style firearms.  When operating a firearm that uses a crank - the operator's arm moves in continous motion.  The operator moves the crank clockwise and a round is fired.   The operator continues to move the crank forward to discharge another round, and so on....  With the SSAR-15; the operator moves the upper assembly forward to discharge a round.  To discharge the next round the operator must again move the upper assembly forward.  Just like when using the Gatlin systems; a semi-auto firearm equipped with the SSAR-15 will never fire automatically.

The SSAR-15 is designed for use on all AR-15 .223/5.56 rifles equipped with a carbine style buffer tube.  There are no permanent modifications or gunsmith required to install the SSAR-15. 

By removing the factory pistol grip and replacing it with the provided Interface Block - the SSAR-15 simply slides onto the buffer tube; replacing the factory adjustable stock.  All tools required to install the SSAR-15 are provided.

Each SSAR-15 comes with a Hex Key to remove the factory pistol grip, Interface Block, SSAR-15 Rifle Stock, BATFE Approval Letter, and Installation / Operation Instructions. The unit is for right handed use only .

Free shipping! No Credit Card fee charges!!

Sorry no shipments to California at this time due to state regulations.

The stock function with calibers other than 556 Nato/.223 but will not function with .22LR.

Check out our website at www.FreedomIndustriesLLC.com

REDACTED

title: For Sale:  Spanish Modelo 1895 cavalry saber
postcontent:
For sale is one Spanish Modelo (model) 1895 cavalry saber.  It is marked with the cartouche of the Spanish sword armory the Artilleria De Toledo in Toledo Spain.

The Model 1895 was the cavalry saber issued to Spanish cavalry units during the Spanish-American was and was replaced by the Modelo 1907 which became the inspiration for the U.S. Patton Calvary Saber. 

The Modelo 1895 represents a transitional period in cavalry sword design where the curved slashing swords of the Napoleonic period moved towards a straight lance like blade. Its grip, shaped to the human hand was a unique innovation for its time. The Modelo 1895 retains a slight curve while it has been lengthened from previous models. 

This sword has a lovely patina, intact wooden grips, and a bright sheath.  Sheath has dings, which is normal for this type of construction and consistent with age. Sword has light pitting, and has been coated with Renaissance Wax.  Sword serial number is 31095. 

This sword is $ 300.00. Cash Only

You can view another example of the same model here: 
http://arms2armor.com/Swords/span1895.htm
